Every vector has two different representations, one referred to as contravariant component (
  
    
      
        
          V
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle V^{i}}
  ) with a covariant basis (
  
    
      
        
          
            
              
                Z
                →
              
            
          
          
